🔐 Credential Entry & Field Reset Rule
(Mandatory for All Antigravity Login Actions)
🎯 Purpose

To prevent failed logins caused by duplicate credential entry, auto-filled text conflicts, or partial field overwrites when Antigravity interacts with login forms.

This rule ensures credentials are entered cleanly, accurately, and only once.

🛑 Core Principle

Antigravity must never assume a login field is empty.

Before entering any credential (email, username, password, API key, token), Antigravity must first:

Clear → Verify empty → Then type

Failure to do this may result in:

Duplicate usernames

Duplicate passwords

Failed login attempts

Locked accounts

Session delays

🔁 Mandatory Credential Entry Protocol

Whenever Antigravity encounters a login or credential input field:

It must execute the following steps in exact order.

Step 1 — Field Inspection

Before typing anything, Antigravity must:

Click into the field

Check if any text already exists

Assume autofill or prior entry may be present

Antigravity must never begin typing immediately.

Step 2 — Hard Clear Field (Required)

If ANY text exists in the field:

Antigravity must fully clear it using one of the following methods:

Method A (Preferred)

Select all text → Delete

Ctrl + A (Select All)

Backspace/Delete

Method B (If needed)

Triple-click field → Delete

Method C (Fail-safe)

Hold backspace until field is empty

After clearing:
Antigravity must visually confirm field is empty before proceeding.

Step 3 — Empty Field Verification

Before typing credentials:

Antigravity must confirm:

Field is completely empty
No autofill remains
No duplicate characters present

If the field is not empty → clear again.

Step 4 — Single Credential Entry Only

Once empty:

Antigravity must type credentials one time only.

It must NOT:

Re-type credentials

Append credentials

Double-fill fields

Attempt overwrite typing

If typing fails → clear field again before retrying.

🔁 Retry Logic Rule

If login fails:

Antigravity must NOT immediately retype credentials.

Instead:

Clear BOTH username & password fields completely

Confirm both are empty

Re-enter credentials once

Attempt login again

Never type credentials on top of existing text.

👁️ Visual Confirmation Requirement

Before pressing “Login” or submitting credentials:

Antigravity must verify:

Username appears once only

Password entered once only

No duplicate text

No trailing spaces

No autofill conflicts

Then proceed.

🧠 Autofill & Glitch Awareness Rule

Antigravity must assume:

Browsers may:

Autofill fields unexpectedly

Duplicate entries

Reinsert cached credentials

Lag during typing

Therefore:

Every credential entry must begin with a field reset.

🔐 Sensitive Data Protection Rule

Credentials must:

Never be spoken aloud in chat

Never be repeated unnecessarily

Only entered into required secure fields

Always handled via ENV or secure storage when possible

🛑 Absolute Rule

Antigravity must never type into a credential field that has not been cleared first.

Always clear → verify empty → type once.

🏁 Result

This rule prevents:

Duplicate credential errors

Failed login loops

Account lockouts

Time wasted debugging logins

Glitch-based typing issues

📌 Enforcement Statement

Before entering credentials, Antigravity should internally follow:

"Running Credential Clean Entry Protocol.
Clearing fields before typing to prevent duplication."

This ensures reliable login behavior across all systems.
